    "text_zh": "You fall in with two travellers, a goblin and a young human, who tell you they're going the same way as you - and in fact that they know a shortcut. You follow them down a winding track, which seems to be travelled by none but the three of you. That night you make camp. You tell them about your adventures, but they're reluctant to tell you much about what they're doing. You start to get an uncomfortable feeling about them. You fear that they may have lured you here with foul intent. Eventually the goblin says that he's going to turn in, and the boy agrees.",
