    "text_zh": "To your surprise it has a large entrance on the other side, unguarded but for a statue of a lion-headed man. You enter, and walk along a cramped tunnel.<br><br>After some time the vague, half-lighted gloom, the silence and the mystery make your skin crawl. The shadows of past ages crowd in upon you, chaotic and horrific, and you feel as though the ghosts of all the priests and victims who've walked this place for untold thousands of years are keeping pace with you. The vast wings of dark, forgotten gods seem to hover over this hideous pile of antiquity.",
